LAGOS – The Muslim Pilgrims Welfare Board, on Monday, called on intending pilgrims to come forward for registration and commencement of payment for the year 2021 Holy pilgrimage to Mecca and Medinah. A release signed by the Executive Secretary of the Board, Alhaji Salau Babatunde indicated that intending pilgrims are to pay initial Hajj fare deposit of N1.2million in not more than three instalments. The release advised intending pilgrims that intends to rollover their initial 2020 Hajj fare deposit to visit the Board for proper documentation. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Besides, it enjoined other intending pilgrims to pay all necessary fares, saying that attendance would be accorded priority on the basis of first-come-first-serve and urged members of the public with enquiries to visit the Board office at the New Secretariat Complex, Block B, Oke-Mosan, Abeokuta for further information. The release also announced the commencement of the Hajj Savings Scheme designed for those who intend to build their savings over a period of time, towards performing Hajj.